
Prompt 2.1.3: Create Mock Data
Objective: Generate realistic mock data for development.
Instructions for AI Agent:

Create a mock data file in src/lib/mockData.ts with realistic sample data:

1. Create mock categories (at least 8):
   - Examples: Gaming, Education, Entertainment, Music, Sports, Technology, Cooking, Travel

2. Create mock tags (at least 20):
   - Examples: tutorial, review, gameplay, funny, vlog, etc.

3. Create mock videos (at least 50):
   - Each video should have:
     - Unique ID (use UUID format strings)
     - Realistic title
     - Description (2-3 sentences)
     - Thumbnail URL (use placeholder image service like https://picsum.photos/320/180)
     - Duration (between 60-3600 seconds)
     - Random view count (100-100000)
     - Upload date (within last 6 months)
     - Random uploader
     - Random category
     - 2-5 random tags
     - Random like/dislike ratio

4. Create mock users (at least 10):
   - Mix of regular and premium users
   - Use realistic usernames

5. Create mock comments (at least 30):
   - Distribute across videos
   - Some with replies (nested comments)

6. Export helper functions:
   - getVideos(filters: VideoFilters): { videos: Video[], pagination: PaginationData }
   - getVideoById(id: string): Video | undefined
   - getCategories(): Category[]
   - getTags(): Tag[]
   - getCommentsByVideoId(videoId: string): Comment[]

7. Implement basic filtering and sorting logic in getVideos():
   - Filter by category if provided
   - Filter by tags if provided
   - Sort according to sortBy parameter
   - Paginate results

DELIVERABLE: Complete mock data file with realistic data and helper functions.